r1667900, which added *_mutex_timedlock() and friends, seems to have broken "#include <apr_thread_mutex.h>" if it is the first APR header to be included.

The reason is that apr_thread_mutex.h now depends on apr_time.h, which eventually ends up circularly depending on apr_thread_mutex_t (which has not been defined yet) through apr_allocator.h. The reproduction program is easy enough:

  #include <apr_thread_mutex.h>
  int main() { return 0; }

As of r1732328, mod_http2 in httpd no longer compiles against APR-2/trunk because of this issue.
